fields.text: At what time did people start voting at your polling stream? (if voting has not commenced by 9am complete a critical incident form)

Was the polling stream set up so that voters could mark their ballot in secret?
(if "No" complete a critical incident form)
Did the polling stream have the following materials?(if any materials are missing complete a critical incident form)
Indelible Markers
Three Ballot Boxes (Presidential, National Assembly and Local Government)
Presidential Ballot Papers - Orange
Parliamentary/National Assembly Ballot Papers - Red
Local Government Ballot Papers - Black and White
Official Stamp/Mark
Final Voters' Register
Polling Booths
How many polling officials were present at the polling stream?
How many political party polling agents were present at the polling stream?
Was a polling agent present for MMD?
Was a polling agent present for Patriotic Front?
Was a polling agent present for UPND?
Were uniformed police present at the polling stream?

Were all ballot boxes present shown to be empty before they were closed and sealed?
(if "No" complete a critical incident form)
How many people are registered at the polling stream?
What is the ECZ's six digit ID number of the polling station of your polling stream?
How many people with a NRC and voter's card were not permitted to vote because their name did not appear on the voter's register
How many people were permitted to vote even though they did not have their NRC and voter's card?
How many people were permitted to vote even though their name was not in the voter's register?
How many people who requested assistance in voting were denied assistance?
How many people were permitted to vote on behalf of someone other than themselves?
How many people who voted were not marked with indelible ink after voting?
At any time, did any campaigning occur inside the polling stream?
At any time, were uniformed security personnel in the polling stream without permission of the election officials?
At any time, were unauthorised persons permitted in the polling stream?

Were there any incidents of intimidation or violence at the polling stream? 
(if "Yes" complete a critical incident form)

At any time, was the voting process suspended for more than 30 minutes?
(if "Yes" complete a critical incident form)
How many people were in still in the queue waiting to vote at 18h00?
Was everyone in the queue waiting to vote at 18h00 permitted to vote?
Was anyone permitted to join the queue and vote after 18h00?
Were the opening slots of all ballot boxes sealed closed after everyone had voted?

Were all polling agents permitted to observe the counting of ballot papers?
(if "No" complete a critical incident form)

Were any unauthorized persons present during counting?
(if "Yes" complete a critical incident form)

Were there any incidents of intimidation during counting? 
(if "Yes" complete a critical incident form)
